      <section eId="sec_CCRP-102">
        <num>CCRP 102</num>
        <heading>102. Â Autopsy</heading>
        <subsection eId="CCRP-102__subsec_1">
          <num>(1)</num>
          <content>
            <p>When there is a reasonable probability that the violation of a criminal statute has contributed to the death;</p>
          </content>
        </subsection>
        <subsection eId="CCRP-102__subsec_2">
          <num>(2)</num>
          <content>
            <p>When ordered by the court, which order may be issued ex parte by the court either on its own motion or on application by the district attorney; or</p>
          </content>
        </subsection>
        <subsection eId="CCRP-102__subsec_3">
          <num>(3)</num>
          <content>
            <p>In all other cases provided by law.</p>
          </content>
        </subsection>
        <authorialNote marker="source">
          <p>Source: https://www.legis.la.gov/legis/Law.aspx?d=112318</p>
